<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>AIR CONDITIONING - HEATER SYSTEM: 2000, 4000, AND 8000 - Before 12/06/1994 - REMOVE AND INSTALL - BLOWER
        MOTOR AND LOW/HIGH PRESSURE SWITCH RELAYS
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="0">
        <title>BLOWER MOTOR AND LOW/HIGH PRESSURE SWITCH RELAYS</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>The blower motor and low/high pressure switch relays are located on the passenger side, in front of
                the Blend-Air unit.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Remove</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the battery ground cable.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the cover from the passenger side of the instrument panel.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Using an offset screwdriver socket, remove the relay mounting screws and remove the
                    relay(s) from the air duct.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect the wiring harness connectors from the relay(s).</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Install</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Connect the wiring harness to the relay(s).</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Position the relay(s) on the air duct and install the mounting screws. Use an offset
                    screwdriver or a socket to tighten these screws.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reconnect the battery cable.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Turn the key switch to ON and check the operation of the relay(s). After this operation
                    check, turn the key switch OFF.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Replace the instrument panel cover.</para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
